  "prompt": "Why is adoption expensive?",
  "response": "Adoption can be expensive for several reasons:\n\n1. Legal fees\n- Lawyer costs for paperwork and legal proceedings\n- Filing and court documentation expenses\n\n2. Agency administrative costs\n- Screening and matching processes\n- Background checks\n- Home study preparations\n- Staff salaries\n\n3. Birth mother expenses\n- Medical care during pregnancy\n- Counseling services\n- Living expenses in some cases\n\n4. International adoption factors\n- Travel costs\n- Foreign agency fees\n- Government documentation\n- Translation services\n- Immigration processing\n\n5. Foster care adoption\n- Required training programs\n- Home study expenses\n- Background investigations\n\n6. Regulatory compliance\n- Extensive background checks\n- Multiple professional evaluations\n- Meeting state and federal requirements\n\n7. Matching and placement services\n- Professional counseling\n- Coordination between birth parents and adoptive parents\n- Ongoing support services\n\n8. Type of adoption\n- Private adoptions tend to be more expensive\n- Domestic adoptions differ from international adoptions\n- Infant adoptions typically cost more than older child adoptions\n\n9. Extensive screening processes\n- Ensuring child's safety\n- Verifying prospective parents' suitability\n- Comprehensive medical and psychological evaluations\n\nThese factors contribute to the overall high cost of adoption.",
